LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 101
BY STATE AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 STATING FINDINGS OF THE LEGISLATURE AND REJECTING THE RATES OF LEGISLATIVE
3 COMPENSATION SET BY THE CITIZENS' COMMITTEE ON LEGISLATIVE COMPENSA-
4 TION.
5 Be It Resolved by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 WHEREAS, the Legislature is vested with the authority to reject or re-
7 duce rates of compensation and expenses established for service as members
8 of the Legislature by the Citizens' Committee on Legislative Compensation
9 pursuant to the provisions of Section 23, Article III of the Constitution of
10 the State of Idaho; and
11 WHEREAS, with Idahoans facing increasing costs for essential goods and
12 services such as food, housing, and energy, the Legislature must exercise
13 fiscal responsibility by prioritizing the needs of Idaho residents over in-
14 creasing government growth and higher legislator compensation.
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED by the members of the First Regular
16 Session of the Sixty-eighth Idaho Legislature, the Senate and the House
17 of Representatives concurring therein, that the rates of compensation for
18 services rendered as members of the Legislature, as set by the Citizens' Com-
19 mittee on Legislative Compensation on November 6, 2024, to take effect for
20 the two-year period beginning December 1, 2024, are hereby rejected, and the
21 rate of compensation and expenses in effect during the Sixty-seventh Idaho
22 Legislature are continued in full force and effect. The compensation and
23 expenses that were in effect from December 1, 2024, until the effective date
24 of this resolution shall be deemed to have been in effect for that period, and
25 any amounts paid shall have been paid lawfully and need not be recovered from
26 or repaid by members of the Legislature.

